{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"47daab2a-a2ed-46f4-8e22-97f3d584b4d5","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter editing, run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything resolves. Check for any NuGet packages that need version bumps for .NET 11 compatibility (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"60d768a9-0554-44e8-af9a-c387718b48ee","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search files since they described their setup.","outputTokens":269,"requestId":"8857:28FA24:1DEEE5D:216286B:69FA9D60"},"id":"44cfda9c-c0ab-4ccd-9e10-48810fbec589","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:46:14.876Z","parentId":"3c9fd905-dd1e-4d97-9561-3e665eaf77dd"}
